Class PairTimeComparator

  • java.lang.Object
    • PairTimeComparator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<PairTime>

    public class PairTimeComparator
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<PairTime>
    PairTimeComparator is used to compare two PairTime objects. Since two PairTime objects may have identical field values but be references to different objects, this class implements methods to test these objects for equality.

      • compareLists

        public int compareLists(java.util.ArrayList<PairTime> pt1,
                        java.util.ArrayList<PairTime> pt2)
        Compares two ArrayLists of PairTime objects for equality. This method will ensure that, if a PairTime object exists in one ArrayList, a PairTime object with identical fields exists in the other ArrayList.
        Parameters:
        pt1 - the first PairTime object to be compared
        pt2 - the second PairTime object to be compared
        Returns:
        0 if the ArrayLists are equal; 1 if the ArrayLists are not equal
